Deji Lambo One more body was on Thursday recovered by emergency responders at the site of the explosion in Abule-Ado, Amuwo-Odofin Local Government Area of Lagos State. This brings the death toll to 21 as 17 corpses were recovered on Sunday when the incident occurred, while three more were found on Monday. PUNCH Metro had reported that some of the victims of the explosion were still missing as their family members were seen at the scene of the tragedy unsure of their whereabouts. The Director-General, Lagos State Emergency Management Agency, Dr Oluwafemi Oke-Osanyintolu, while confirming the recovery of the corpse on Thursday, stated that the explosion displaced 468 persons from their homes. He stated, “The teams continue to carry out recovery and salvage operations at the incident site. An additional body was retrieved today (Thursday), bringing the total number of fatalities to 21. “A total of 468 persons were displaced from their homes and 100 of them are now in a relief camp. Two persons are missing. Our help desk is manned and our personnel are available to manage enquiries and arrange transfer to the LASEMA relief camp for those who have need for shelter and food. “We appeal for calm and urge members of the public to keep away from the scene. “We will continue to provide updates.” Copyright PUNCH.
